				<td rowspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" style="text-align: justify;" width="100%" valign=top>
				<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>I've run into a problem with the "Basic Training" task from the tutorial.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I've had a low-level rogue for a long time before the new tutorial was made (his original purpose was to run around Kaladim harvesting mushrooms so my main could use them for making Kaladim Constitutionals). Though I never really played him aside from that, I'd occasionally pass a few items down that my other characters had either outgrown or couldn't use. As a result, at some point, his starting Dagger* got deleted to make way for better items.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I recently moved him into the tutorial to run him through some of the tasks when I was bored, but could never finish the Basic Training task...more specifically, the step where you give your weapon to Absor to have it upgraded. I obviously cannot do that because I no longer have the weapon he accepts, and cannot buy it anywhere since I believe it is NODROP.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So my question is: is there any way those few of us who have lost or otherwise discarded that weapon can get another one, either through a hail, perhaps a kill, perhaps an equivalent tradeable item can be added, etc. Alternatively, perhaps we could just skip this step by telling him we [do not need an upgrade] or something.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>I know it's probably not a big deal, and the task works fine for other alts I've created afterwards and kept their starting weapons. But it's going to drive me crazy to not be able to finish it. <img src='/i/smilies/16x16_smiley-happy.gif' width=16 height=16 border=0> Thanks.</DIV>
				
